  "prompt": "What are some of the best Soft Rock songs of all time?",
  "response": "Soft rock is a genre known for its melodic sound and laid-back vibe. Here are some of the best soft rock songs of all time:\n\n1. **\"All Out of Love\" - Air Supply**  \n2. **\"You've Got a Friend\" - James Taylor**  \n3. **\"Babe\" - Styx**  \n4. **\"Dreams\" - Fleetwood Mac**  \n5. **\"Make It with You\" - Bread**  \n6. **\"Killing Me Softly with His Song\" - Roberta Flack / The Fugees**  \n7. **\"Just the Way You Are\" - Billy Joel**  \n8. **\"I Don't Want to Talk About It\" - Rod Stewart**  \n9. **\"Rich Girl\" - Hall & Oates**  \n10. **\"Say You Love Me\" - Fleetwood Mac**  \n11. **\"What a Fool Believes\" - The Doobie Brothers**  \n12. **\"If\" - Bread**  \n13. **\"Linda\" - Jack Jones**  \n14. **\"Landslide\" - Fleetwood Mac**  \n15. **\"Sara\" - Jefferson Starship**  \n16. **\"Sweet Caroline\" - Neil Diamond**  \n17. **\"How Deep Is Your Love\" - Bee Gees**  \n18. **\"The Air That I Breathe\" - The Hollies**  \n19. **\"I Want to Know What Love Is\" - Foreigner**  \n20. **\"Winds of Change\" - Scorpions**  \n\nThese songs highlight the signature sound of soft rock, characterized by smooth vocals, gentle melodies, and emotional lyrics. Many of these tracks have remained popular across generations, resonating with listeners for decades.",
